Appeal of Joint Meeting of DPRK Government, Parties and Organizations Hailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 22 (KCNA) -- Papers here today carry commentaries in support of the appeal of the joint meeting of the DPRK government, political parties and organizations.
 The appeal to the 70 million fellow countrymen, which was adopted at the meeting on Jan. 19, set the slogan "Let us pave a wide avenue for independent reunification through national cooperation under the banner of our nation-first spirit!" as the slogan for the country's reunification to be held high by the Korean nation and put forward 5-point task to implement it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun in a signed commentary says that the appeal is being supported and welcomed at home and abroad as it reflects the ardent desire and will of all the fellow countrymen to smash the aggression and war moves of the U.S. imperialists, defend the peace of the country and give impetus to the process of reconciliation and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The commentary notes: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The main issue discussed at the joint meeting is that the whole Korean nation should take practical actions to cope with the nation's confrontation with the U.S. under the banner of the Korean nation-first spirit. The time has come to settle a final account with the U.S. trying to bring disasters of nuclear war to the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The five-point task is to fully demonstrate the dignity of the Korean nation on the basis of its superiority, positively realize national cooperation, dynamically wage a sacred anti-U.S. patriotic struggle, thoroughly implement the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and uphold the great Songun politics. It is the most key and essential issue to win victory in the anti-U.S. patriotic struggle for reunification this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our nation-first spirit is the banner of victory in the drive to carry out the task. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that the 5-point task and the proposal for implementing it is a patriotic initiative to defend the peace of the country and pave a wide avenue for independent reunification.

National Preparatory Committee of Nepal Formed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 22 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of a Nepalese national preparatory committee for commemorating the Day of the Sun and celebrating February 16, birthday of leader Kim Jong Il, was held in Kathmandu on January 15.
 At the ceremony Ram Prid Paswan, vice-president of the Nepalese Senate, was elected chairman of the preparatory committee and it was decided to organize colorful political and cultural functions from February to April. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the preparatory committee said that the birthdays of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il are global holidays and that they would most grandly commemorate the birthdays of the great leaders of the progressive humankind of the world in all sincerity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the ceremony.

U.S. Hostile Policy toward DPRK Condemned by Czech Organization 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 22 (KCNA) -- The Paektusan Czech-Korean Friendship Association sent a letter to the U.S. president on January 9 in denunciation of the U.S. imperialists' hostile policy toward the DRPK.
 The letter said that the United States is making much ado about "nuclear threat" from the DPRK, but the nuclear crisis in the Korean peninsula was caused by the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has illegally deployed nuclear weapons in and around south Korea and frequently staged aggressive military exercises against the DPRK, the letter pointed out, stressing that the U.S. can never evade its responsibility for killing a large number of Koreans in cold blood during the 1950-1953 Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the U.S. troops have no justification for occupying south Korea, the letter strongly demanded that the U.S. unconditionally withdraw its troops from south Korea and accede to the DPRK proposal to settle the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. in a peaceful way.

Rodong Sinmun on Driving Force of Peace Movement 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 22 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article says that the master of the movement for defending peace is the popular masses and they have decisive strength to push ahead with it.
 The popular masses of all the countries are directly in charge of the peace movement, the article says, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is important to enhance the role of the popular masses of all the countries, the driving force of the peace movement, in order to prevent aggression and war and defend peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The popular masses should wage a powerful anti-imperialist and anti-war struggle with the consciousness of being the driving force of the peace movement. The danger of war is increasing in different regions and countries and peace is seriously threatened due to the moves of the U.S. imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Imperialists never give up aggression and war.
 Peace can be provided only when all the peace-loving people of the world who value independence turn out as one to wage a resolute and stubborn struggle against the aggression and war policy of the imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is important for the popular masses of all the countries to allow no aggression and war of the imperialists, halt their arms race and arms build-up and wage a firm struggle to drive their military bases and aggression troops out of other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unity of the popular masses of all countries is a decisive guarantee for strengthening their position and enhancing their role as the main force of the peace movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the progressive forces and peace-loving people of the world should unite under the anti-imperialist and anti-war banner for peace to jointly counter the increasing moves of the U.S.-led imperialists for aggression and war and make a collective counterattack on the imperialists in all regions where their tentacles of aggression have reached. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the popular masses of all countries aspiring after independence and peace, to firmly maintain the anti-imperialist stand for independence is the basic demand for the unity of the peace-loving forces and the main guarantee for them to enhance their role as the driving force of the peace movement to more successfully wage the anti-war struggle for peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will in the future, too, unite with the popular masses of all the countries under the anti-imperialist and anti-war banner for peace to stage an energetic struggle against the moves of the imperialists for aggression and war in defence of peace in Asia and the rest of the world.

Proposal of Joint Meeting Supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 22 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Dae, chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Social Democratic Party (KSDP), in a statement on January 21 said that an important issue to take practical actions to cope with the Korean nation's confrontation with the U.S. was discussed at the joint meeting of the DPRK government, political parties and organizations, and expressed full support to it.
 The politicians of the north and the south should share intention and keep step with each other with a view to smashing the aggression moves of the U.S., the common enemy of the north and the south, and shaping out the advance road of the Korean nation under the present situation that frontal confrontation between war and peace, division and reunification, is going on between the entire Korean nation and the U.S., he said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KSDP will energetically materialise solidarity with many political parties and organizations at home and abroad in response to the appeal of the joint meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will make all efforts to realize national cooperation through solidarity, and travels and contacts between the political parties and organizations of the north and the south irrespective of ideology, political views and religious belief. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the fellow countrymen in the north and the south and overseas should unanimously trust in and uphold the great Songun politics, the genuine patriotic politics, in order to defend the dignity and sovereignty of the Korean nation and achieve peace and reunification of the country under the uplifted banner of our nation-first spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The entire members of the KSDP will energetically turn out to carry through the slogan for national reunification set forth in the joint New Year editorial in keeping with the growing desire of the fellow countrymen for reunification. He expressed the belief that all the fellow countrymen in the north and the south and overseas would positively respond to the appeal to the 70 million Koreans.

Posters for 8th Kimjongilia Festival
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 22 (KCNA) -- New posters were created for the 8th Kimjongilia Festival to be grandly opened on the occasion of the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il (Feb. 16), the greatest holiday of the Korean nation.
 Written in the upper part of the posters are letters "Celebration February 16." Brought into relief against the background of brilliant rays of light and beautiful firecrackers is Kimjongilia, the immortal flower in full bloom carrying the unanimous desire of the Korean people and the world revolutionary people who are boundlessly praising and following Kim Jong Il, great leader, iron-willed commander and tender-hearted father.
 Painted in the low part of posters are a flag symbolic of the festival and the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition in which the festival will be held. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letters "The 8th Kimjongilia Festival" and a period of the festival are seen in posters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The posters encourage all the Korean people and servicemen to harden their faith and will to build a great prosperous powerful nation in this land true to the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il.

KCNA Comments on Japan's Move for "New Defence Program"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 22 (KCNA) -- The Japanese government decided to introduce the MD system and has planned to fundamentally examine the readjustment of defence power and the existence mode of the "Self-Defence Forces" and map out a "new defence program" this summer.
 The "guidelines on re-examination of defence power" decided at a recent security council meeting and a ministerial meeting of the Japanese government set forth the policy to counter the "new threat" of terrorism and missiles and further strengthen defence power for "peace and security of the international community." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is said that the "SDF" will change into an organization for multi-purpose operations including the "activities for international cooperation" besides the defence of Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such movement clearly shows the political reality of Japan putting spur to the moves to become a military power and set out on overseas aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is now actively pushing ahead with the moves to become a military power, pursuant to the U.S. move to establish the MD system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's Defence Agency is about to get a budget of 800 billion ~ 1 trillion yen for the maintenance of interceptor missiles Patriot-3 and Aegis missiles to establish the MD network. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan keeps dispatching the "SDF" overseas under the pretext of war against terrorism and, in particular, sending heavily armed troops of the "SDF" to the Iraqi war field under the signboard of assistance to post-war reconstruction of Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's move to work out the "new defence program" this year is intended to fix by law the present political reality, in which Japan is setting out on the road of overseas expansion with the backing of the U.S. indulged in hegemonic high-handed practices after the September 11 incident and lay a foundation to erase the article banning war in the "peace constitution" and change it into a war constitution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Phrases "coping with the new threat" and "activities for international cooperation" are nothing but a camouflage to legalize the arms buildup of Japan and overseas aggression of the "SDF." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is proved by the fact that Japan has escalated the position and mission of the "SDF" for "international cooperation" while intending to deploy a long-distance transport plane and large transport ship for overseas dispatch. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the facts indicate that the final target of the "new defence program" is to convert the "SDF" equipped with latest military hardware into the elite aggression force capable of performing overseas mobile military operations worldwide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Asian countries and the international community are standing guard over Japan's move to officially change its defence policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Japan hastens the move to become a military power and the way of reinvasion, overheated by its ambition for militaristic overseas expansion in the new century instead of liquidating its blood-stained history of aggression on Korea and other Asian countries, it would precipitate its final destruction.
